Khda 2012 Assessment Results for Dubai schools are an eye-opener. Here's a quick summary of the Good vs. Very Good vs. Excellent results.

When we started, we had no intentions to become a value-addition school. It just happened as we were mid-stream. We continue to modify our programs to stay relevant in the changing educational landscape.

This is just a letter to accompany your copy of Khda's 2012 Assessment Results for Dubai Schools. It's a PDF that recognizes the effort that you have put in over the past year. Feel free to download it and share it.

We all know that Dubai's most recent property crash was in 2008 and none of us are interested in a repeat, but a lot of people are hoping to be able to purchase their first home in the next 2-3 years.

I may have to qualify that statement. Schools fill-up before Handover on 15th of January, but the school takes a bit of time to settle down smoothly (programs, extra-curricular activities). All seems well, but after a few months, it may seem like locusts have invaded and nothing is working out.
